# Allowlist (deny-by-default) for the bare dotfiles repo.
# Everything under $HOME is ignored by default so an accidental
# `dotfiles add .` / `dotfiles add -A` stages nothing.
#
# To start tracking a new file, force past this ignore:
#     dotfiles add -f <path>
#
# Note: `add -f` overrides this file, so a typo'd force-add can still
# stage a secret. This guards bulk adds, not explicit force-adds.
*

# Keep this allowlist itself visible/tracked.
!.gitignore
